text:
Love their homemade noodle soup no.10 ! You have to try it ! Don't pack ! Consume there while it is hot ! Fantastic value at $4 /bowl including an egg !
Their minced meat ramen Shanghainese style is great too no.7 at $4.50/bowl ! One of my daughter's favorite! Lastly remember to order their dumplings (deep fried or boiled) too .
It is worth the trip ! Support our hawkers !
They sell frozen dumplings too ! Look at the queue  !

Gan Lao Ramen $5.
Ramen was soggy & lumpy. Fried dumplings were soggy & chewy. Everything else is MSG overloaded.

I've enjoyed their mee hoon kueh more than once. I find it tasty, affordable, and value for money. The mee hoon kueh also has a nice springy bite which I like.

It is one of the very few stalls that opens into the night at this food centre.
Portion is generous with refreshing soup and pack-filled fishball. The taste bit sour and not too spicy which is not really to my liking

They speciality is soups, but they have also dumplings, which are the best in the Empress Market. The sauce is amazing! (ginger with vinegar i guess) You can get them fried or boiled as a main dish or with a noodle soup. They cost 3sgd for 6 pieces.
